<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7666901>
    bibo:endPage "124" ;
    bibo:journal "African Invertebrates" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2004-12-31" ;
    bibo:startPage "21" ;
    bibo:volume "45" ;
    dc:creator "Londt, Jason G. H." ;
    dc:date "2004" ;
    dc:title "A review of the afrotropical genus Gonioscelis Schiner, 1866 (Diptera: Asilidae), with descriptions of new species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7666945>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7666965>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7666919> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7666945>
    dc:description "Figs 113–133. Gonioscelis male genitalia. 113–115. G. tomentosus Oldroyd, 1970 (34 mi. E of Kenge). 113. Lateral. 114. Dorsal. 115. Ventral. 116–118. G. truncatus Oldroyd, 1974 (Van Reenen paratype). 116. Lateral. 117. Dorsal. 118. Ventral. 119–133. G. ventralis Schiner, 1867. 119–121. Holotype. 119. Lateral. 120. Dorsal. 121. Ventral. 122–133. Gonocoxal variation. 122. Holotype. 123. Cradock (femoralis). 124. Bulawayo (rufescens). 125. Louterwater. 126. Vivo. 127. Tugela Ferry. 128. Padkloof. 129. Gravelotte. 130. Boknes. 131. Alicedale. 132. Grahamstown. 133. Mseleni. Scale lines = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7666945/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7666965>
    dc:description "Figs 148–149. Distribution of Gonioscelis species found only in southernAfrica. 148. closed circle = genitalis, open circle = longulus, closed square = maculiventris, open square = phacopterus. 149. closed circle = lacertosus, open circle = nigripennis, closed square = ramphis, open square = truncatus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7666965/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7666919>
    dc:description "Figs 18–29. Gonioscelis male genitalia. 18–20. G. amnoni sp. n. (holotype). 18. Lateral. 19. Dorsal. 20. Ventral. 21–23. G. batyleon sp. n. (holotype). 21. Lateral. 22. Dorsal. 23. Ventral. 24–26. G. bykanistes sp. n. (Hotazel paratype). 24. Lateral. 25. Dorsal. 26. Ventral. 27–29. G. ceresae Oldroyd, 1974 (holotype). 27. Lateral. 28. Dorsal. 29. Ventral. Scale lines = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7666919/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

